When two aircraft are converging at approximately the same level, the aircraft
that has the other on its right shall give way, except as follows:
a) power-driven heavier-than-air aircraft shall give way to airships, gliders
and balloons;
b) airships shall give way to gliders and balloons;
<) gliders shall give way to balloons;
d) power-driven aircraft shall give way to aircraft which are seen to be towing
