When rapidly changing meteorological conditions make it inadvisable to include
a weather report in the ATIS, the ATIS messages shall indicate that the relevant
weather information will be given on initial contact with the appropriate ATS unit.

Information contained in a current ATIS, the receipt of which has been
acknowledged by the aircraft concerned, need not be included in a directed transmission
to the aircraft, with the exception of the altimeter setting.

